AT 022300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A LARGE SLOW-MOV AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE LIES WITH CENTRE
NORWEGIAN SEA 1027 RIDGING S TOWADS THE AZORES WHILST SLACK LOW PRESSURE
LIES ACROSS MOST OF THE CONTINENT. BY MIDDAY TUESDAY THE PATTERN REMAINS
SIMILAR WITH HIGH PRESSURE LYING TO THE N W AND SW OF THE UK AND LOW PRESSURE
ACROSS THE CONTINENT. OVERNIGHT WEAK LOW MAY MOV E TOWARDS SW IRELAND EVENTUALLY
CUTTING THE HIGH INTO TWO CENTRES N AND S OF THE UK AND MERGING WITH THE
LOW ACROSS THE CONTINENT BY MIDDAY WEDNESDAY.
THE PATTERN BECOMES SLOW-MOV AGAIN THEREAFTER WITH SLACK LOW PRESSURE
NOW CENTRED ROUGHLY ACROSS THE S OF THE UK WITH PIVOTAL CENTRE 1006 TO THE
SW. HIGH PRESSURE REMAINS TO THE N OF THE UK AND ALSO ACROSS THE AZORES.
